<title>WANDER-RANDOMLY-IN-COMPASS-DIREC</title>

</head>
<body>

	<h3><i>I repeatedly wander both left and right as well as up and down. Note 

	that this micro-behaviour is defined as the composition of two other 

	micro-behaviours.</i> </h3>

	<p><font size="2" color="gray">Begin micro-behaviour</font>
	</p>
	<p><b>WANDER-RANDOMLY-IN-COMPASS-DIRECTIONS</b></p>

	<font size="2" color="gray">Begin NetLogo code:</font>
	<pre>add-behaviours list-of-micro-behaviours "Behaviours" [WANDER-HORIZONTALLY.html WANDER-VERTICALLY.html]</pre>
	<font size="2" color="gray">End NetLogo code</font>
	<h2>Related Micro-behaviours</h2>


	<p>This combines

	<a title="WANDER-HORIZONTALLY" href="WANDER-HORIZONTALLY.html">

	WANDER-HORIZONTALLY</a> and

	<a title="WANDER-VERTICALLY" href="WANDER-VERTICALLY.html">

	WANDER-VERTICALLY</a>.</p>

	<p>

	<a title="WANDER-RANDOMLY-BY-TURNING" href="WANDER-RANDOMLY-BY-TURNING.html">

	WANDER-RANDOMLY-BY-TURNING</a> is alternative way of moving by going forward 

	and turning.</p>

	<h2>How this works</h2>

	<p>This adds the behaviour of randomly moving north or south 1 step and the 

	behaviour of randomly moving east or west 1 step.</p>

	<h2>History</h2>



	<p>This was implemented by Ken Kahn</p>
